HEADWORD: Troche
<hw>Tro"che</hw> <pr>(tr⟦omac⟧"k⟦emac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>trocho`s</grk> anything round or circular, a wheel, properly, a
runner, fr. <grk>tre`chein</grk> to run. Cf. <er>Trochee</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Pharm.)</fld> <def>A medicinal tablet or lozenge; strictly, one of
circular form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

